.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-9-12::.
4 different games are played: snooker, backgammon, go, bridge
4 different pets are kept: chinchilla, hamster, snake, ferret
1. the person playing snooker is on the right of the person playing go##1
2. the person playing go is not to the left of the owner of the ferret##8
3. the person playing bridge and the owner of the hamster have the same parity positions##9
4. the owner of the ferret is the person playing bridge##1
5. the person playing snooker is somewhere to the right of the owner of the chinchilla##5
6. the owner of the snake is on the left of the person playing bridge##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |  1   |   2   |   3   |     4      |
| Music-Genre   | backgammon  | bridge  | go | snooker    |
| Transport     | snake | ferret | chinchilla  | hamster |

