.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-9-18::.
City: san-francisco, berlin, hannover, new-york
There 4 different types of food: lime, kiwi, cranberry, cabbage
1. the person traveling to new-york and the person eating lime have the same parity positions##9
2. the person eating cranberry is on the left of the person eating kiwi##1
3. the person traveling to hannover is not to the right of the person eating lime##8
4. the person traveling to new-york is not to the right of the person traveling to berlin##8
5. the person eating lime is in an even position##4
6. the person eating cranberry and the person traveling to san-francisco have the same parity positions##9
7. the person eating lime and the person traveling to hannover have the same parity positions##9

.:: Answer ::.
|       |      1      |   2    |     3      |       4        |
| Job   | san-francisco | new-york | berlin | hannover |
| Pet   | cranberry    | kiwi   | cabbage        | lime            |

